class Shape3D an abstract class for three-dimensional objects such as cubes, prisms, cylinders and spheres.
class Point a class for points. A point doesn't have a dimension.
class Line a class for lines. A line doesn't have an end.

class CurvedShape -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- an abstract class for curved two-dimensional shapes. Trait TComparable applied here because we wanted to have type-checking through parameters. For example, curved shapes can only be accepted in the related methods.

class Polygon an abstract class for polygon. Trait TComparable applied here because we wanted to have type-checking through parameters. For example, polygon shapes can only be accepted in the related methods.

Polygon 0..1 -> 3..* vertices Point
A Point called vertices may have a Polygon. It can have none or just 1.
A Polygon has at least3 Points called vertices and can never have none. And there is no upper bound defined.
